<% var pageTitle = 'NamelessUnSee - Privacy Policy'; %>
<%- include('partials/legal-head', { pageTitle: pageTitle }) %>

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Last updated: 2026-07-19. This instance is operated by
    <strong><%= operator.name %></strong><% if (operator.jurisdiction) { %> (<%= operator.jurisdiction %>)<% } %>.</p>

  <div class="warn">
    <strong>Plain statement.</strong> When you view shared content (an image or
    video), this service logs everything it reasonably can about your visit and
    burns identifying details into the copy shown to you. We do not hide this.
    This page, the
    <a href="/tos">Terms</a>, and the warning page do not log you and load nothing
    but their own text, the site font, a small self-hosted script that reveals the
    operator's contact address (it runs entirely in your browser and makes no
    network requests), and (on the warning page) a self-hosted bot check. If
    enabled by the deployment, Cloudflare Insights may also be injected by the
    edge and is permitted by the page policy.
  </div>

  <h2>1. Roles</h2>
  <p>For personal data collected from viewers of a shared image, the person who
    uploaded and shared that image is the data <em>controller</em>; the operator of
    this instance provides the platform and acts as a <em>processor</em> on their
    behalf, and is the controller for account data and site operation. <br>
    Contact: <% if (contactObfuscated) { %><strong><span data-obfuscated-email="<%= contactObfuscated %>">(the
    contact address appears here once JavaScript loads)</span></strong><% } else { %>the
    operator of this instance<% } %>.</p>

  <h2>2. What we do NOT collect on legal pages</h2>
  <p>The warning page, this Privacy Policy, and the Terms perform no application
    logging and no application geolocation. Cloudflare Insights may be injected
    by the edge if enabled by the deployment. Collection by this application
    begins only after you pass the warning page and continue to an image.</p>

  <h2>3. What is collected when you view a shared image</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Network:</strong> your public IP address, IP-based geolocation
      (country, and region/city and network operator/ASN where available).</li>
    <li><strong>Connection type:</strong> whether your connection appears to be a
      VPN, proxy, Tor exit, or datacenter/hosting network. Such connections are
      refused, and access is refused where your connection cannot be identified.</li>
    <li><strong>Device and request:</strong> your User-Agent and other HTTP request
      headers (excluding credentials such as cookies and authorization headers), and
      the browser, operating system, and device type derived from them.</li>
    <li><strong>Browser-exposed details (via a small script):</strong> screen and
      window dimensions, colour depth, pixel ratio, timezone and offset, languages,
      platform, CPU core and device-memory hints, touch-point count, cookie-enabled
      flag, Do-Not-Track signal, network-connection hints reported by the browser,
      User-Agent Client Hints where available, WebGL vendor and renderer where
      exposed, browser feature availability, display preferences, storage quota
      and usage estimates, navigation/paint timing, battery state and timing
      hints where available, media decoding capability results, a small fixed
      set of font feature checks, and the referring page. Keystrokes, entered
      text, click or interaction counts, clipboard contents, camera,
      microphone, and device permission grants are not collected.</li>
    <li><strong>Event:</strong> the time of the view and the image reference.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This information is written to an access log <em>and</em> is rendered as a
    visible watermark into the copy of the image shown to you.</p>

  <h2>4. Account data</h2>
  <p>If you register, we store your email address, username, a hashed (scrypt)
    password- never the plaintext- your role, rank, and approval status, account
    timestamps, your upload preferences and any per-account limits, and the IP
    address of your most recent login (used for security and abuse prevention,
    including bans). Email 2FA and account recovery (password, email, or username)
    store short-lived challenge records; only a hash of each code is stored. If
    you opt into TOTP, we store the authenticator secret needed to verify codes;
    it never leaves the server.</p>

  <h2>4a. Uploaded media and moderation</h2>
  <p>Uploaded originals are encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM) before being written
    to storage, and are never served to viewers- only watermarked copies are.
    At upload time, media may be scanned <em>locally on the server</em>: a
    perceptual fingerprint (hash) of the media is computed and compared against an
    operator-managed blocklist, and an optional content classifier may run,
    also locally. No upload content is sent to a third party for scanning.
    Flagged uploads are queued for review by administrators. The fingerprint and
    moderation status are stored with the image record.</p>
  <p><strong>Administrator access:</strong> site administrators can retrieve the
    original, un-watermarked file of any upload- for moderation review, abuse
    handling, and site operation. The guarantee that the original is never served
    applies to viewers; it does not limit administrators of the instance.</p>

  <h2>4b. Leak reports</h2>
  <p>Account holders may report unauthorised redistribution of media they shared.
    A report stores the reporter, the affected image, the reason and details
    given, uploaded screenshot evidence, and- when the report is filed against a
    specific logged view- a link to that access-log entry. Reports are visible
    to administrators for review and enforcement.</p>

  <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consent cookie</strong>- a signed session cookie recording that you
      accepted these terms; it is cleared when you close your browser, so the warning
      is shown once per session.</li>
    <li><strong>Session cookie (<code>sid</code>)</strong>- set only if you log in;
      signed, HTTP-only, used to keep you signed in.</li>
    <li><strong>2FA and recovery challenge cookies</strong>- short-lived, signed,
      HTTP-only cookies used only while completing a login verification or account
      recovery challenge (including a temporary cookie that enforces a cooldown on
      repeated verification emails).</li>
    <li><strong>View-gate cookie</strong>- a short-lived (about 10 minutes),
      signed, HTTP-only cookie set after you pass the bot check on an image's view
      page; it is scoped to that image and marks that the check was completed.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>No advertising, analytics, or third-party tracking cookies are used.</p>

  <h2>6. Why we collect it (purposes and legal bases)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tracing and deterring unauthorised redistribution</strong> of shared
      images, and refusing anonymised access- the core function. Legal basis:
      your <strong>consent</strong>, given at the warning page, together with the
      uploader's legitimate interests.</li>
    <li><strong>Providing accounts and the service</strong>- basis: performance of a
      contract and legitimate interests.</li>
    <li><strong>Security, abuse prevention, and enforcement</strong> (including bans)
     - basis: legitimate interests and, where applicable, legal obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. No third-party sharing of your IP; no per-viewer external calls</h2>
  <p>Your IP address is not sent to any third party to view an image. Proxy/VPN/Tor
    detection and geolocation are performed locally on the server using datasets the
    server downloads in advance (for example, MaxMind GeoLite2 and public IP lists);
    those downloads do not include your data. Access logs and watermarked copies for
    an image are available to the account holder who shared that image and to site
    administrators. We do not sell or "share" personal information for cross-context
    behavioural advertising.</p>
  <p>The operator may use the following service providers as processors for site
    operation (none of them receives viewer access logs or un-watermarked media):</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email delivery (Resend):</strong> account-related emails- signup
      notices to administrators, login verification codes, and account recovery
      codes- are sent through Resend, which processes the recipient email address
      and the message content for delivery. If email delivery is not configured on
      an instance, no data is sent to Resend.</li>
    <li><strong>Hosting and network (e.g. Cloudflare):</strong> instances are
      typically served through a reverse proxy or tunnel, whose provider processes
      connection metadata (such as IP addresses) to route traffic. An instance may
      also be configured to store <em>encrypted</em> media objects in Cloudflare R2;
      the storage provider receives only encrypted bytes, and the decryption key
      stays on the operator's server.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Retention</h2>
  <p>Shared images are deleted automatically according to their retention settings
    (a time limit and/or a maximum number of views). An image's access logs are kept
    with the image record and are removed when that record is removed. Leak reports
    and their screenshot evidence are retained until resolved and removed by the
    operator. Account data is retained for the life of the account. The operator
    may retain limited records longer where necessary for security or to comply
    with legal obligations.</p>

  <h2>9. International transfers</h2>
  <p>Data is processed on the operator's infrastructure<% if (operator.jurisdiction) { %>
    in <%= operator.jurisdiction %><% } %>. Where the operator transfers data across
    borders, they are responsible for using an appropriate transfer mechanism.</p>

  <h2>10. Your rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, correct, delete,
    restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data, to data portability,
    and to withdraw consent (which does not affect processing already carried out).
    Under the GDPR/UK GDPR you may also complain to a supervisory authority. Under the
    CCPA/CPRA you may request access to and deletion of your personal information and
    are entitled not to be discriminated against for exercising these rights; we do
    not sell your personal information. To exercise any right, contact
    <% if (contactObfuscated) { %><strong><span data-obfuscated-email="<%= contactObfuscated %>">(the
    contact address appears here once JavaScript loads)</span></strong><% } else { %>the
    operator<% } %>. Requests about a specific shared image may be directed to the
    uploader as controller, and the operator will assist as processor.</p>

  <h2>11. Do Not Track</h2>
  <p>We record the presence of your browser's Do-Not-Track signal as part of the
    logged visit, but because collection here is the explicit, consented purpose of
    the service, a DNT signal does not by itself disable it- if you do not consent,
    do not continue past the warning page.</p>

  <h2>12. Children</h2>
  <p>The service is not directed to children and is not intended for anyone under the
    age of majority in their jurisdiction.</p>

  <h2>13. Changes</h2>
  <p>This policy may be updated; the "last updated" date will change accordingly.</p>

  <p class="foot muted"><a href="/">Back</a> - <a href="/tos">Terms of Service</a></p>
</div>
<% if (contactObfuscated) { %>
<script src="/altcha-obfuscation.min.js"></script>
<script src="/email-reveal.js"></script>
<% } %>
</body>
</html>
